    "remarks": {
      "sha256": "887003feda6a9164696adc10b6c26b34ede113e410fd7c9c531e3764d65e62fa",
      "source_region": "div.problem-additional-text",
      "text": "Erd\\H{o}s and Graham knew this with $e^{-cK}$ replaced by $c/K^2$."
    },
    "statement": {
      "sha256": "4c9522dd3c9f0427ceecc8ba67e0b9697a3721f6421f7e2ff308a162ae6bf9a0",
      "source_region": "div#content",
      "text": "Does there exist some $c>0$ such that, for any $K>1$, whenever $A$ is a sufficiently large finite multiset of positive integers with $\\sum_{n\\in A}\\frac{1}{n}>K$ there exists some $S\\subseteq A$ such that\\[1-e^{-cK} < \\sum_{n\\in S}\\frac{1}{n}\\leq 1?\\]"
    }
  },
